dataIdInfo.idAbs: Annual Five-Year Age Group Population Estimates by Sex for 2015 to 2030 for the national and first-order administrative division levels of Rwanda were prepared by the U.S. Census Bureau for joining (linking) to shapefiles as attribute data. The estimates are consistent with the midyear national projections from the U.S. Census Bureau International Data Base (IDB).
dataIdInfo.idPurp: The U.S. Census Bureau is providing annual subnational five-year age group population estimates by sex for Rwanda for 2015-2030 in a geographic information system (GIS) for users of the Spatial Data Repository, funded by the U.S. President’s Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief (PEPFAR).
dataIdInfo.idCredit:
CENSUS DATA 2012 Age-Sex Data: Fourth Population and Housing Census - 2012, Topic: Demography, Population, "Total Population, Number" (includes age and sex data for area levels 4 and 5). National Institute of Statistics of Rwanda. Originally downloaded from http://www.devinfo.statistics.gov.rw/di7web/libraries/aspx/dataview.aspx (no longer available online, accessed March 11, 2021).
2002 Population Total Data: Fourth Population and Housing Census - 2012, Provisional Results (includes final 2002 population totals). National Institute of Statistics of Rwanda. Available online at http://www.statistics.gov.rw/publication/rphc4-provisional-results (accessed November 03, 2021).
The U.S. Census Bureau cannot guarantee the accuracy of non-U.S. census and survey data.
GEOSPATIAL BOUNDARIES International boundaries coincide with the Large Scale International Boundaries (LSIB) dataset from the U.S. Department of State, Office of the Geographer and Global Issues. Available online at http://geonode.state.gov (accessed November 04, 2021).
Geospatial data for the first-order administrative divisions of Rwanda were downloaded from the Humanitarian Data Exchange, available online at http://data.humdata.org/dataset/rwanda-administrative-boundaries-level-1-4, "Rwanda - Subnational Administrative Boundaries" (accessed November 04, 2021).
The U.S. Census Bureau cannot guarantee the accuracy of boundary placements.
NATIONAL ESTIMATES AND PROJECTIONS U.S. Census Bureau, Population Division. International Data Base, December 2020 release, available online at http://www.census.gov/data-tools/demo/idb/ (accessed November 01, 2021).
NATIONAL AND SUBNATIONAL AREA NAMES AND CODES (1) U.S. National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency. NGA GEOnet Names Server (GNS), available at http://geonames.nga.mil/gns/html/ (accessed November 02, 2021). Contains geographic area names from the U.S. Board on Geographic Names and the U.S. Government Federal Information Processing System (FIPS) codes. (2) U.S. Government Geopolitical Entities, Names, and Codes (GENC) Standard. NSG Standards Registry, available at http://nsgreg.nga.mil/genc/discovery (accessed November 02, 2021).

Consts.useLimit: U.S. Census Bureau population estimates: None. Acknowledgment of the Census Bureau would be appreciated in products derived from its population estimates. The subnational boundaries used for this shapefile were downloaded by the U.S. Census Bureau from a publicly available source for this product. The international boundaries are derived from the Large Scale International Boundaries (LSIB) dataset (public domain).

dataIdInfo.suppInfo:
SUBNATIONAL DIVISIONS Rwanda's first-order administrative divisions: 5 provinces as of the 2012 census.
SHAPEFILES The original shapefile downloaded from the Humanitarian Data Exchange had 416 polygons and matched the 2012 census sectors (third-order administrative divisions), after a change to the subnational boundaries by USCB staff: (1) A polygon was added by USCB staff representing the portion of Lake Kivu that falls within the international boundary of Rwanda.
This change resulted in a shapefile with 417 polygons, one for each of Rwanda's third-order administrative divisions, and one for Lake Kivu. The U.S. Census Bureau aligned the shapefile's national boundary to the Large Scale International Boundary Line (LSIB) polygon file from the U.S. Department of State, Office of the Geographer and Global Issues. Finally, the LSIB-aligned shapefile was dissolved into 6 polygons, one for each of Rwanda's first-order administrative divisions (5 provinces) as reported by the National Institute of Statistics of Rwanda in the 2012 census, and one for Lake Kivu.
FEATURE AND ATTRIBUTE DETAILS The 2015-2030 population estimates for Rwanda's administrative divisions are provided in the following two tables: (1) The Unicode tab-delimited text file (table) "Rwanda_5yr_age_sex_2015-2030_uscb_jan2022.txt," which can be joined to the shapefile via the common field "GEO_MATCH." (2) The Excel table "Rwanda_5yr_age_sex_2015-2030_508_uscb_jan2022.xlsx," formatted for accessibility in compliance with Section 508 of the U.S. Government's Federal Rehabilitation Act.
Details on processing of the census data and calculation of 2015-2030 estimates are provided in the "Census Metadata" tab of the Excel file and "Methods for Calculating 5-Year Age Group Population Estimates by Sex for Subnational Areas" document. For the subnational areas, the U.S. Board on Geographic Names (BGN) "approved" names from the NGA GEOnet Names Server (cited in the "Credits") were used. For any area that a BGN name was not available, the name from the national census was used. Official codes for the subnational areas from the country's national statistical office, when available, are entered in the "NSO_CODE" field in both the text and Excel tables. Information on any alternative area names or recent name or boundary changes is entered in the "USCBCMNT" field. A partial list of the fields in the Excel and Unicode text files, including all fields identifying geographic names and codes, is provided in the Excel file's "Data Dictionary" tab. More detail on the U.S. Census Bureau subnational age and sex group estimates and maps for PEPFAR can be found in the document "Subnational Population Estimates Components for the Spatial Data Repository." It includes a data dictionary that is similar to that in the Excel table.
METHODOLOGY For more information, see the following methodology documents in the Spatial Data Repository: (1) "U.S. Census Bureau Methodology for SDR Subnational Population Estimates." (2) "U.S. Census Bureau Methods for Calculating 5-Year Age Group Population Estimates by Sex for Subnational Areas." (3) "Instructions for Joining Subnational Population Data to Shapefiles."
ACCESS The U.S. Census Bureau’s products for PEPFAR can be accessed from the Spatial Data Repository at http://spatialdata.dhsprogram.com/home/, which also provides access to data and maps from the DHS (Demographic and Health Surveys) Program. A zipped file containing shapefiles with metadata, an Excel workbook with subnational population estimates, and a Unicode tab-delimited text file is available for each country. PEPFAR products are also available on the Census Bureau website at http://www.census.gov/geographies/mapping-files/time-series/demo/international-programs/subnationalpopulation.html for download.
